
	## Sonarqube

		## Docker UI
		- docker run --rm -it --name sonarqube -p 9000:9000 sonarqube:community
		- docker run --rm -it --name sonarqube -p 9000:9000 
			   -v ~/sonarqube/data:/opt/sonarqube/data \
			   -v ~/sonarqube/extensions:/opt/sonarqube/extensions \
			   -v ~/sonarqube/logs:/opt/sonarqube/logs \
			   sonarqube:lts

		## Access
		- http://localhost:9000
		- Default user credentials
			admin:admin

		## Documentation
		- https://docs.sonarsource.com/sonarqube-server/latest/

		## Scan local proyect
		- Create file in de root directory of the local proyect with name: sonar-project.properties
		- Content:
			sonar.projectKey=my_project
			sonar.projectName=My Project
			sonar.projectVersion=1.0
			sonar.sources=.
			sonar.host.url=http://localhost:9000
			sonar.login=<TOKEN_GENERADO>

		## Docker Scaner
		- docker run --rm -it -e SONAR_HOST_URL="http://${SONARQUBE_URL}" -e SONAR_TOKEN="myAuthenticationToken" -v "${YOUR_REPO}:/usr/src" sonarsource/sonar-scanner-cli
		- SONARQUBE_URL=172.17.0.1

